    "summary": "Chaw-Ming Lee is an interim consultant / auditor / analyst with extensive experience in both financial and IT audit & control engagements, built from his experience at several of the worlds leading accounting firms. Throughout his career he has sought to combine core audit experience with related regulatory compliance, legal, IT as well as operational accounting knowledge in order to offer his clients an integrated services proposition of high quality.\n\nNext to his main focus of interim consulting services, Chaw Ming has founded his own accounting company serving small business with tax an accounting support, with a special focus on the Chinese business community.\n\nChaw-Ming has specific experience in Financial Accounting and Auditing, IT audit support (GITC), Information Security, IT Business Process Redesign, Due Diligences, Vendor / Software Selection, Data Analysis (IDEA), Tax & Legal advisory.  In the last few years Chaw-Ming has participated in major SOx compliance projects for KPN and Getronics and has extensive experience with process & risk analysis, walkthroughs and Operational Effectiveness testing. As such he has experience in working in interdisciplinary and multi-national teams.\n\nChaw-Ming aims for client-mindedness in all his professional activities. He also has committed himself to continuously improve his professional experience knowledge and level of professional certification. He is a member of the professional associations NOREA, ISACA and OOA (aspiring member) and he currently holds the EMITA RE title for EDP auditing. \n\nChaw-Ming is fluent in English, Dutch and Chinese (Mandarin and Cantonese).\n\nSpecialties: \n\u2022 Project / Program Management\n\u2022 IT Financial Audit/ Accounting\n\u2022 Information Security Consulting/ Auditing\n\u2022 IT Policy development\t\n\u2022 Threat and vulnerability analysis\n\u2022 ISO27001 and General IT controls reviews \n\u2022 Application Control reviews\n\nCo-Founder of Silk Tree Consulting",
